entry.title: Revert "[SavedTabGroups] Listen to changes from sync for tabs."
entry.content:
This reverts commit e1e631d81673e79873891cc5496254fa5d82d80e.



Reason for revert: SavedTabGroupBarBrowserTest.ValidGroupIsOpenedInTabstripOnce is consistently failing in "Linux" and "Linux ChromeOS" MSan builders.



It's a use-of-uninitialized-value in saved_tab_group_web_contents_listener.cc:45:7



Failure: https://paste.googleplex.com/6709289505783808?raw



Example build: https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chromium/builders/ci/Linux%20MSan%20Tests/40034/test-results?q=ID%3Aninja%3A%2F%2Fchrome%2Ftest%3Abrowser_tests%2FSavedTabGroupBarBrowserTest.ValidGroupIsOpenedInTabstripOnce+&sortby=&groupby=







Original change's description:

> [SavedTabGroups] Listen to changes from sync for tabs.

>

> LocalTabGroupListener::UpdateFromSync updates the local group to match the saved group when updates are received from sync, handling adds, removes, navigations, and reorders. Unit tests are added for adding, removing, and navigating, as well as removing the group, but not for reordering, as the sync-side implementation of that is not complete.

>

> Reordering tabs in a group is implemented in UpdateFromSync, but as those changes aren't yet being synced, so it doesn't work end-to-end.

>

> Also, this CL includes a couple of fixes to the sync bridge and model to propagate sync changes correctly when the group is removed via sync.

entry.title: [iOS][byot] Move bottom message view out of the regular tabs grid view
entry.content:
Previously, the regular tabs bottom message is owned by the grid view

controller for regular tabs. This was designed since both were only

shown when the user was on the regular tab grid, but since the display

and position of the bottom message is really controlled by the tab grid

view controller, weird animation issues would happen.



This CL puts the bottom message back into the tab grid view controller

instead of the GridViewController for the regular tabs, and fixes

animation bugs in the process. Bugs fixed:



1. Tapping "incognito" and "remote" buttons not working when the

prompt is visible, because "viewDidLayoutSubviews" would "scroll" the

page back to regular.

2. Closing tabs from when the tabs are more than the screen could hold

to when the tabs would not fill the tab grid screen would NOT hide the

bottom message. This issue used to happen because the offset of the

grid view controller doesn't seem to be updating properly. (Actually

the exact root cause is not identified yet.)



Fixed: 1441885

IsInactiveTabsAvailable is the kill-switch for the feature.

IsInactiveTabsEnabled is the kill-switch AND if the use disabled the

feature in the app's settings.



InactiveTabsCoordinator, InactiveTabsMediator, and

InactiveTabsViewController are all created at startup when the feature

is available, even if the user disabled it in settings, so they should

check for IsInactiveTabsAvailable.

entry.title: [Files]: Fix sticky query
entry.content:
The success callback holds onto the query parameter from the closure in

which it was constructed. As a result, it is possible for the

onSearchCompleted_ callback to be called while it is holding onto the

old query value. Then it goes into the loop. The store is updated with

the old value, that differs from the current value (empty), which

re-triggers search, with the old query value that now becomes the new

query value.



The fix relies on the fact that we can update part of the search state.

We only mark it as success, with no update to the query. This breaks the

loop.

entry.title: Stay away from fragment-less boxes during paint / pre-paint.
entry.content:
Some layout boxes have no fragments, which means there's nothing to

paint or hit-test. This may happen for:



* Excess children of LayoutNGFrameSet (i.e. LayoutFrame or

LayoutNGFrameSet) that don't fit within the grid defined by the

frameset

* LayoutNGTableColumn (never creates fragments)

* LayoutNGView (iframes in certain states)



The test included doesn't actually crash without the code in this CL,

since we already had some guards against fragment-less boxes. Without

CL:4392606 and CL:4236260 it would crash, though.



This CL also makes us bail in pre-paint at fragment-less boxes, so

that the paint property tree builder can assume that a LayoutBox always

has fragments (in an upcoming CL).

entry.title: Update AppApiTest to reconcile with ProcessPerSiteUpToMainFrameThreshold
entry.content:
The ProcessPerSiteUpToMainFrameThreshold feature allows renderers

to share processes with a restriction that a process may only be

shared while the number of main frames in that process stays below a

threshold. The assumption of the feature is that when renderers share

process under the threshold, responsiveness wouldn't be regressed.



This CL makes AppApiTest ensure that apps are hosted in a different

process only when the ProcessPerSiteUpToMainFrameThreshold is disabled, because the reason to separate process is to improve responsiveness.



Please refer to https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/4493583/comment/3cb9c010_96cef9d7/ for the context.

entry.title: Scale size and area by max DPI value for non-square DPI PrintSettings
entry.content:
PrintSettings stores paper size and printable area in device units. The

device units for most platforms is the DPI multiplied by inches. For

printers with non-square DPI, the largest DPI value should be used.



When converting job settings to PrintSettings, the paper size and

printable area were scaled by their respective dimension's DPI instead

of the max DPI value. This meant that X and Y axes were represented

differently in paper size and printable area. Print Preview does not support rendering different dpi settings in the X and Y axis, so this

was causing incorrect renderings.



Fix places where the paper size and printable area should be scaled by

the max DPI.

entry.title: crostini: Re-enable multi-container app badging
entry.content:
The crostini multi-container feature (currently behind flag) allows

users to install apps within different Linux containers. Previously

users were able to differentiate apps installed in different

containers using a user-defined colour dot (See screenshots below), but

this regressed recently.



This CL adds GuestOS's ApplyBadge to the new IconLoader/Reader path so

that the colour dot can be re-enabled. Since the GuestOS method

requires an app_id and profile value to return the badge colour for

a given app, these arguments have been added where necessary.

We are running into occasional ThreadChecker DCHECKs from the

AmplitudePeakDector. It's unlikely that there is a production issue

here (e.g. two threads calling into the peak detector at once):

the AmplitudePeakDetector might be used on a new realtime audio thread

it with a lock, and makes sure there is never contention on this new

lock.

under lock on MacOS, for ease of reasoning.

entry.title: [Multipaste] Notify of item updates when availability changes
entry.content:
Currently, ClipboardHistoryController notifies observers of clipboard

history item update when item(s) are added to, removed from, or

updated in the clipboard history. In fact, ClipboardHistoryController

should also notify observers when clipboard history availability

changes. For example, clipboard history becomes disabled due to

the change in session state.



In this CL, ClipboardHistoryController becomes a session observer so

that the controller can notify observers when the clipboard history

enabling state is toggled.



In addition, in this CL, ClipboardHistoryController posts a task to

notify observers. In this way, observers are only notified of

clipboard history update once if there are multiple changes in a

short duration.



The earlier patch set (before and including patch set 15), an

independent class called ClipboardHistoryDescriptorManager is

created to achieve the same functionality. In the latest patch set,

ClipboardHistoryDescriptorManager is removed and its code logic is

incorporated into ClipboardHistoryControllerImpl.
